claims:
1. A computer-implemented method comprising:
receiving, from a client system, a request to perform a machine-learning communication workflow;
receiving, in association with the request, a set of obfuscated identifiers for which processing via the machine-learning communication workflow is requested, wherein each obfuscated identifier of the set of obfuscated identifiers corresponds to an identification of an obfuscated version of a profile stored at a data management system, the obfuscated version lacking personally identifiable information (PII);
for each obfuscated identifier in the set of obfuscated identifiers:
mapping the obfuscated identifier to a non-obfuscated identifier that identifies a non-obfuscated version of the profile that includes PII;
retrieving, from the data management system, user data from the non-obfuscated version;
executing a trained machine-learning model to process at least part of the user data corresponding to the non-obfuscated version of the profile that includes the PII;
identifying one or more communication specifications based on the execution of the trained machine-learning model;
causing a first content to be transmitted to a destination address identified in the user data in accordance with the one or more communication specifications, wherein a time of the transmission of the first content, a type of communication transmission used for the transmission of the first content and/or part or all of the first content correspond to the one or more communication specifications;
receiving one or more new communications, each of the one or more new communications having been transmitted from a user device in response to the transmission of the first content, wherein the user device is associated with the destination address;
extracting field values from the one or more new communications, wherein the extracted field values identify new user-activity data collected from the one or more new communications;
causing a second content to be transmitted to the destination address, wherein the second content includes the extracted field values from the one or more new communications;
receiving, from the user device and in response to the transmission of the second content, one or more indications as to which of the extracted field values added information to the obfuscated versions of the profiles associated with the set of obfuscated identifiers; and
further training an implementation of the trained machine-learning model using the one or more indications.
2. The method of claim 1, wherein the new user-activity data indicate a particular type of user action performed on the first content.
3. The method of claim 1, wherein the new user-activity data include header data identifying a type of the user device, a location of the user device, and/or browsing history of the user device.
4. The method of claim 1, wherein the extracted field values indicate that the new user-activity data were collected as a result of executing the trained machine-learning model.
5. The method of claim 1, wherein the extracted field values indicate the one or more communication specifications used to transmit the first content.
6. The method of claim 1, wherein the one or more indications are determined based on a comparison between an extracted field value of the extracted field values and a field value separately identified by the user device.
7. The method of claim 6, wherein the comparison includes:
determining that the extracted field value is different from the field value separately identified by the user device;
determining that the extracted field value was generated at a later time relative to a time when the field value was separately identified by the user device;
indicating that the extracted field value has added information to the obfuscated versions of the profiles associated with the set of obfuscated identifiers; and
further training the implementation of the trained machine-learning model using at least the extracted field value as an input.
